20 (b) (1) (i) Subject to subparagraph (ii) of this paragraph, each
21 cannabis–related website shall employ a neutral age–screening mechanism that verifies
22 that the user is at least 21 years old, including by using an age–gate, age–screen, or age
23 verification mechanism before the user may access or view any content and before the
24 website may collect the user’s address, e–mail address, phone number, or contact
25 information to disseminate advertisements.
26 (ii) If a website is appropriate for a qualifying patient who is under
27 the age of 21 years, the website shall provide an alternative screening mechanism for the
28 qualifying patient.
29 (2) An advertisement placed on social media or a mobile application shall
30 include a notification that an individual must be at least 21 years old to view the content.
31 (3) The provisions of this subtitle applicable to cannabis licensees may not
32 be avoided by hiring or contracting with a third party, or outsourcing advertisements that
33 do not comply with this subtitle.

